4 SYNOPSIS:
5 This bill would establish the Gun Violence
6 Protective Order Act.
7 This bill would authorize courts to issue ex
8 parte gun violence protective orders and one-year gun
9 violence protective orders, which may be authorized if
10 the court finds that the respondent, as defined, poses
11 an immediate and present danger of causing personal
12 injury to self or others.
13 This bill would provide that upon the issuance
14 of an ex parte or one-year gun violence protective
15 order, the court shall order the respondent to
16 surrender to the local law enforcement agency all
17 firearms and ammunition of which the respondent has
18 custody, control, ownership, or possession.
19 This bill would provide for the renewal or early
20 termination of a one-year gun violence protective order
21 under certain conditions.
22 This bill would provide criminal penalties for a
23 violation.
24
