244 Section 6. (a) A petitioner requesting a one-year gun
245 violence protective order shall include in the petition
246 detailed allegations based on personal knowledge that the
247 respondent poses a substantial danger of causing personal
248 injury to self or others through his or her ownership,
249 purchase, control, possession, or receipt of a firearm or
250 ammunition.
251 (b) Prior to a hearing for a one-year gun violence
252 protective order, the court shall do both of the following:
