291 Section 7. (a) A respondent subject to a one-year gun
292 violence protective order may submit one written request at
293 any time during the effective period of the order for a
294 hearing to terminate the order.
295 (1) Upon receipt of the request for termination, the
296 court shall set a date for a hearing. Notice of the request
297 shall be served on the petitioner in accordance with the
298 Alabama Rules of Civil Procedure. The hearing shall occur no
299 sooner than 14 calendar days from the date of service of the
300 request upon the petitioner.
301 (2) The respondent seeking termination of the order
302 shall have the burden of proving by a preponderance of the
303 evidence that the respondent does not pose a substantial
304 danger of causing personal injury to self or others through
305 his or her ownership, purchase, control, possession, or
306 receipt of a firearm or ammunition.
307 (3) If the court finds that the respondent has met his
308 or her burden, the court shall terminate the order.
Page 11

or her burden, the court shall terminate the order.
SB156 INTRODUCED
309 (b) A petitioner may request a renewal of a one-year
310 gun violence protective order at any time within the three
311 months before the expiration of the order.
312 (1) A court, after notice and a hearing, may renew the
313 one-year gun violence protective order if the court, by a
314 preponderance of the evidence, finds that the respondent
315 continues to pose a substantial danger of causing personal
316 injury to self or another through his or her ownership,
317 purchase, control, possession, or receipt of a firearm or
318 ammunition.
319 (2) In determining whether to renew a one-year gun
320 violence protective order, the court shall consider all
321 relevant evidence presented by the petitioner, and may also
322 consider other relevant evidence, including, but not limited
323 to, evidence of the events identified in Section 5(d).
324 (3) A one-year gun violence protective order renewed
325 under this subsection shall expire after one year, subject to
326 termination by further order of the court at a hearing held
327 under subsection (a) and further renewal by order of the court
328 under this subsection.
329 Section 8. (a) Upon issuance of an ex parte or one-year
330 gun violence protective order, the court shall order the
331 respondent to surrender to the local law enforcement agency
332 all firearms and ammunition of which the respondent has
333 custody, control, or ownership.
334 (b) A law enforcement officer serving a gun violence
335 protective order shall request that all firearms and
336 ammunition belonging to or in the custody or control of the
Page 12

ammunition belonging to or in the custody or control of the
