368 Section 9. (a) As used in this section, "dispose" means
369 to sell or transfer a firearm or ammunition to a federally
370 licensed dealer, defined under 18 U.S.C. § 921 et seq., or to
371 destroy the firearm or ammunition.
372 (b) Thirty days before a one-year gun violence
373 protective order is set to expire, a law enforcement agency
374 holding a firearm or ammunition that has been surrendered
375 pursuant to the order shall notify the petitioner that the
376 order is set to expire. The notice shall advise the petitioner
377 of the procedures for seeking a renewal of the order pursuant
378 to Section 7.
379 (c) If a gun violence protective order is terminated or
380 expires and is not renewed, a law enforcement agency holding
381 any firearm or ammunition that has been surrendered pursuant
382 to Section 8 shall notify the respondent that he or she may
383 request the return of the firearm or ammunition. The law
384 enforcement agency shall return any surrendered firearms or
385 ammunition requested by a respondent only after confirming,
386 through a background check, that the respondent is currently
387 eligible to own or possess firearms and ammunition.
388 (d) A respondent who has surrendered a firearm or
389 ammunition to a law enforcement agency pursuant to Section 8
390 and who does not wish to have the firearm or ammunition
391 returned or who is no longer eligible to own or possess a
392 firearm or ammunition may sell or transfer title of the
