405 (f) A law enforcement agency holding a firearm or
406 ammunition that was surrendered by a respondent pursuant to
407 Section 8 may dispose of the firearm or ammunition only after
408 six months from the date of proper notice to the respondent of
409 the intent to dispose of the firearm or ammunition, unless the
410 firearm or ammunition has been claimed by the lawful owner. If
411 the firearm or ammunition remains unclaimed after six months
412 from the date of notice, then no party shall have the right to
413 assert ownership of the firearm or ammunition and the law
414 enforcement agency may dispose of the firearm or ammunition.
415 Section 10. (a) The court shall notify the Alabama
416 State Law Enforcement Agency (ALEA) no later than one business
417 day after issuing, renewing, dissolving, or terminating an ex
418 parte or one-year gun violence protective order under this
419 act.
420 (b) The information required to be submitted to ALEA
