(b) The information required to be submitted to ALEA
SB156 INTRODUCED
421 pursuant to this section shall include identifying information
422 about the respondent and the date the order was issued,
423 renewed, dissolved, or terminated. In the case of a one-year
424 order, the court shall include the date the order is set to
425 expire. The court shall also indicate whether the respondent
426 to the one-year gun violence protective order was present in
427 court to be advised of the contents of the order or if the
428 respondent failed to appear. The respondent's presence in
429 court shall constitute proof of service of notice of the terms
430 of the order.
431 (c) Within one business day of service, a law
432 enforcement officer who serves a gun violence protective order
433 or the clerk of the court shall submit the proof of service
434 and a copy of the protection order to ALEA for entry into the
435 appropriate database.
436 (d) The information to be submitted to ALEA under this
437 section shall be submitted in an electronic format, in a
438 manner prescribed by ALEA. ALEA shall maintain a searchable
439 database of this information, available to law enforcement
440 agencies upon request.
441 (e) Within 30 days of submission of the information
442 under subsection (d), ALEA shall make information about an ex
443 parte or one-year gun violence protective order issued,
444 renewed, or terminated pursuant to this act available to the
445 National Instant Criminal Background Check System for the
446 purposes of firearm purchaser background checks.
447 Section 11. (a) A person who files a petition for a gun
448 violence protective order, knowing the information in the
Page 16

violence protective order, knowing the information in the
SB156 INTRODUCED
449 petition to be materially false or with an intent to harass
450 the respondent, is guilty of a Class C misdemeanor.
451 (b) A person who owns, purchases, controls, possesses,
452 or receives a firearm or ammunition with knowledge that he or
453 she is prohibited from doing so by a gun violence protective
454 order is guilty of a Class C misdemeanor and shall be
455 prohibited from owning, purchasing, controlling, possessing,
456 or receiving, or attempting to purchase or receive, a firearm
457 or ammunition for a period of five years from the date of
458 conviction.
459 Section 12. This act shall not affect the ability of a
460 law enforcement officer to remove firearms or ammunition from
461 any individual pursuant to other lawful authority.
462 Section 13. This act shall not be construed to impose
463 criminal or civil liability on any individual who chooses not
464 to seek a gun violence protective order pursuant to this act.
465 Section 14. This act shall become effective on October
466 1, 2026.
